"My initial pour created two fingers of rocky, bone-white head with excellent retention. Nose was redolent with Old Bay (r) and my mouth instantly began to water. Color was a pretty Yellow-Gold (SRM = 4 - 5) with NE-plus quality clarity. I could see into the future! I could NOT keep my nose out of the glass with this one. This would be fabulous with actual crabs. Mouthfeel was a bit thin, but if it is intended as a Summer Ale, I would not want it to be too full. The taste was of Old Bay (r), but in just the right amount, not overwhelming, which it could have been. How do you describe an ""Ale Brewed with Spices"" when the spices are so variegated? You almost have to have experienced Old Bay (r) seasoning for yourself at some point in order to understand. One point that really needs to be made is its finish. Just like any other beer that relies heavily on spice(s) for its flavor, this was as dry as the desert! This just begs to be drank with some food, especially seafood. Say, Salmon Sunday is tomorrow ..."
