"Dead Rise became famous around my work as the, ""beer with the crabby stuff"" in it. But after trying this one I realized it was no joke at all! Its rich, complex, and a layered wonderfully. The appearance of it is pretty standard with a deep gold color and a medium bodied head. When I took my first smell I was hit with the Old Bay seasoning right away. It was buttery and sweet with a good kick of Old Bay at the end. Nothing too overpowering which I was relieved by. I was also very surprised by how well it tasted! All the flavors blended together wonderfully and gave the beer a great layered experience. First, you get a sweet buttery flavor quickly followed by a smooth tone of Old Bay to season it off. Its really almost the full experience of eating Maryland blue crabs! I'm sure MD locals know what I'm talking about! I'm very pleasantly surprised with this one! I was afraid the Old Bay would be too strong and overpower the beer but it all worked out wonderfully."
